                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2540/16.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Fox</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-07-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 2, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Bacon informs Mr. Fox that in reference to the Guayaquil and Quito Railway
                    Company case the President will be pleased to comply with the wishes of the
                    minister of foreign affairs and will appoint an arbiter at an early date.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
